    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1391359006,
    "creation_date" : 1391359006,
    "answer_id" : 21513103,
    "question_id" : 13670374,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Masood Moshref is right, this error occur because the option menu of Menu is not well prepared by lacking \"return super.onCreateOptionsMenu(menu)\" in onCreate() method.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2584375,
      "reputation" : 8040,
      "user_id" : 2240409,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 79,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0b52128e90fc2a35f1540edd4a9ac06f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "dazito",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2240409/dazito"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1404831745,
    "creation_date" : 1404831745,
    "answer_id" : 24635224,
    "question_id" : 13670374,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>To try to debug this error, first go to your android terminal / console and execute this command:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ps | grep THE_ERROR_PID_YOU_GET_(IT_IS_A_NUMBER)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>then if the output comes out as your app... it is your app causing the error. Try to look for empty <code>Strings</code> that you pass into the <code>layout</code>.</p>\n\n<p>I had this exact same problem and it was my fault as I was passing an empty <code>String</code> into my layout. After changing the <code>\"\"</code> to <code>\" \"</code> this error went away.</p>\n\n<p>If you don't get your app from the console output, then it is something else causing it (probably, as others said, the android keyboard)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2311015,
      "reputation" : 6276,
      "user_id" : 2029134,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/EgAiF.jpg?s=256",
